        <mxCell id="106" value="&lt;b&gt;Step 3&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;RATLB also stops with C16(P) and C19(F).&lt;br&gt;That gives the same bisection interval (C16,C19] as RWLB-S, but it got there through two trigger decisions rather than cumulative sums.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Total: 2 lookback + 1 realized bisect = 3&lt;/b&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;arcSize=6;fillColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#d9d9d9;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=8;fontSize=12;" vertex="1" parent="1">
