        <mxCell id="115" value="&lt;b&gt;Takeaway&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Each panel now shows its own local commit sequence instead of borrowing a single shared history line. FSLB shows pure arithmetic on commit indices. RWLB-S explicitly shows cumulative-risk sums and where they cross T = 1.80. RATLB explicitly shows trigger checks against T = 0.90 and the test on the commit immediately before each trigger. RWLB-S and RATLB still tie here with the same final bracket, but the panelized sequences make it clear that they reach that bracket by different reasoning." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;arcSize=8;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#d9d9d9;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=12;spacingRight=12;fontSize=13;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="1190" width="1580" height="88" as="geometry" />
